Recommended Next Actions
1. Protect Revenue in Premium Skincare (Immediate)
Expedite delayed East shipment and prioritize allocation to East and North.
Rebalance stock from South/West where cover is 11–12+ days.
Implement short-term safety stock increase for premium skincare in high-growth regions.
2. Rebalance and Reduce Excess Budget Inventory (0–60 Days)
Freeze or slow replenishment of budget makeup and slow-moving budget skincare.
Launch tactical promotions or bundles to reduce excess stock.
Reallocate surplus stock to regions with lower cover where feasible.
3. Stabilize Low-Sales Cluster Availability
Adjust minimum stock parameters for budget skincare.
Consolidate replenishment cycles to avoid frequent small stockouts.
Review distribution frequency and order batching logic.
4. Improve Forecast and S&OP Alignment
Introduce a monthly cross-functional demand and supply review (S&OP light).
Focus forecasting improvements on:
Premium skincare (growth bias correction)
Budget makeup (decline adjustment)
Set target to improve forecast accuracy from 78% to >85%.
5. Improve Data and Decision Agility
Integrate sales and inventory data into a single shared planning file or dashboard (short term).
Define clear ownership for stock rebalancing decisions.
Reduce decision lead time for inter-regional transfers.
Overall Management View
The company is experiencing structural imbalance: understocked in high-growth premium skincare and overstocked in declining budget categories.

If not corrected quickly, this will:

Depress service levels further,
Increase excess inventory write-offs,
Constrain working capital,
Risk lost market share in premium segments.
Immediate focus should be on securing premium skincare availability and aggressively managing slow-moving budget inventory, while improving planning integration to prevent recurrence in Q2.
